# font
## Definition
The `font` property is a shorthand property used to set multiple font-related properties in a single declaration.

# CSS Font Properties

| Property | Definition |
|----------|------------|
| `font` | Shorthand property for all font-related properties. |
| `font-family` | Specifies the font or list of fonts used for text. |
| `font-size` | Sets the size of the text. |
| `font-weight` | Sets the thickness (boldness) of the text. |
| `font-style` | Sets the style of the text (normal, italic, oblique). |
| `font-variant` | Displays text in small-caps or other variant forms. |
| `font-stretch` | Expands or condenses the width of a font. |
| `font-size-adjust` | Preserves text readability by adjusting font size based on x-height. |
| `line-height` | Sets the height of a line of text. |

## Most Commonly Used

- `font-family` → Specifies the font type
- `font-size` → Sets text size
- `font-weight` → Makes text bold or lighter
- `font-style` → Makes text italic or oblique
- `line-height` → Controls spacing between lines
- `font` → Shorthand for multiple font properties


Font Shorthand Example
font: italic bold 16px/1.5 Arial, sans-serif;


font-style: italic;
font-weight: bold;
font-size: 16px;
line-height: 1.5;
font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
